'''Noor Al-Deen Mahmoud Ali Al-Rawabdeh''' ({{langx|ar|نُور الدِّيْن مَحمُود عَلِيّ الرَّوَّابدَة}}; born 24 February 1997) is a Jordanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Malaysia Super League]] club [[Selangor F.C.|Selangor]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==International career==
Al-Rawabdeh debuted for the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]] in a 1–1 [[2019 WAFF Championship]] tie with [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]] on 8 August 2019.<ref name="Global Sports Archive 2019">{{cite web | title=Match Report of Kuwait vs Jordan - 2019-08-07 - AsiaCell WAFF Championship | website=Global Sports Archive | date=8 Aug 2019 | url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2019-08-08/kuwait-vs-jordan/1733296/ | access-date=25 Mar 2021}}</ref>

